      <persName role="Photographer"><surname>unknown</surname><ref type="context" target="info:fedora/context:siba.pn.unknown">unknown</ref></persName></ab>
      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">A scout parade in the neighbourhood of Bahçekapı, Fatih. The parade is headed by a boy and a girl scout, each carrying a flag of the Turkish Republic in their right hands and wearing a sash with the motto ‘Ameli Hayat’ (practical life) across their chests. They are flanked by two girl scouts, each carrying a wooden baton of about 1.5 metres in length. More scouts carrying wind instruments and drums follow behind. Bystanders are watching the scene.</ab>
      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet" subtype="comment">The parade most likely took place on the occasion of the Day of Youth and Sports (<ref target="http://gams.uni-graz.at/o:siba.glossar?mode=G7">Gençlik ve spor bayramı</ref>) on 19 May. The motto ‘Ameli Hayat’ indicates that the scouts were affiliated with the school of that name.</ab>
